# download file and save files, here we use a job openings example from https://jobseeker.kalibrr.com/c/nomura-research-institute/jobs/165772/frontend-engineer?similar_job_code=&user_ref=www.kalibrr.com_organic_null_path&job_ref=&app_source=job-board-1-1-15-5048
!wget --quiet https://file.io/nFDlqVqmKy0y

# open the file and read it into a variable job_openings
job_openings = open('nFDlqVqmKy0y', 'r').read() 
    
print ('File downloaded and saved!')

# Next, let's use the stopwords that we imported from word_cloud. We use the function set to remove any redundant stopwords.
stopwords = set(STOPWORDS)

# Next, let's create a word cloud object and generate a word cloud. You can limit the maximum words with max_words
# instantiate a word cloud object
job_wc = WordCloud(
    background_color='white',
    stopwords=stopwords
)

# generate the word cloud
job_wc.generate(job_openings)
